# Cybersecurity Incident Report: SYN Flood Analysis

## Objective
Analyze the provided logs to identify the cause of the website outage and document the findings.

## Context
This documentation was completed with the provided incident and Network logs from the Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate.

## Skilled Demonstrated
- Security Documentation
- Wireshark TCP/HTTP log analysis
- Incident Reporting
- DoS identification

## Tools used
- Google Doc
- Google Sheets providing Wireshark TCP/HTTP logs
- Google Cybersecurity Professional Certificate program

## Scenario 
The company website has experienced a repeated timeout error message. With the TCP/HTTP logs provided, I am tasked to analyze the logs and identify the root cause of the outage.

## Findings
The log data was experiencing a SYN flood attack. The logs showed an extremely large number of SYN requests by a malicious attacker, causing the web server to be completely overwhelmed and preventing legitimate users from connecting and accessing the website.

## Concepts learned
- Three-way handshake connection
- SYN
- SYN/ACK
- DoS attacks
- Network Traffic Analysis

## What I learned
This documentation provided a strong understanding of how to analyze and identify network logs and how SYN flood attacks work.
